commit.message:
drop support for ancient python versions

- libxmp: version: update VERSION_TUPLE to use packaging.version

It would be possible to restore support for these python versions,
by adding code, but because of the limited use of this library, I think
it's for the best to limit supported configurations to common ones.
libxmp: exempi: exempi returns char-sized bool, not int

new for Big Sur M1, look for libexempi.dylib under /opt/homebrew

see https://github.com/Homebrew/brew/issues/9177

Convert the GIF sample file to GIF89a

Exempi >= 2.5 doesn't recognize GIF87a files. This is because XMP uses
the "Application Extension" mechanism which doesn't exist in GIF87a.

Signed-off-by: Nils Philippsen <nils@tiptoe.de>
